      "content": "it's like i'm just staying here out of habit, but there's nothing left of me. i look at the empty side of the bed and i just think... why am i still the one who has to be here? it feels so wrong that i'm still breathing and he's not. it feels like i'm just dragging this heavy, pointless existence around for no reason at all. like the world is just better off without the ache of me being here.",
